\n&gt; that energy and gives it to you, you can indeed benefit from it. But\n&gt; gone are those days and gone are those people. Remember, you&#39;re on your\n&gt; own!\n&gt; &gt;\n&gt; &gt; Forget special yantras, forget special maalaas, forget special idols,\n&gt; and forget rituals done by priests. Have faith, have confidence and do\n&gt; sadhana by yourself on a regular basis.\n&gt; &gt;\n&gt; &gt; The most effective and safest sadhana to do by oneself is homam (fire\n&gt; ritual). Download the homam manuals (see site below) and try a homam on\n&gt; a regular basis.\n&gt; &gt;\n&gt; &gt; Or pick a mantra and do japam with it mentally everyday for an hour or\n&gt; so, while sitting still with closed eyes and an erect back. If your\n&gt; knees hurt, sit on a chair or sofa comfortably, but keep the back\n&gt; straight and eyes closed.\n&gt; &gt;\n&gt; &gt; * * *\n&gt; &gt;\n&gt; &gt; There are many generic mantras (see my original mail at the bottom for\n&gt; a sample list) that are appliable to everybody and can solve ALL\n&gt; problems. For example, Vishnu sahasranaama stotra explicitly says it can\n&gt; solve ANY problem. Instead of looking for a &quot;perfect mantra\n&gt; recommendation&quot;, you can pick a generic mantra like that and start\n&gt; sadhana. The key is faith and persistence.\n&gt; &gt;\n&gt; &gt; If your kaarmik blockage is the size of a rock, small amount energy\n&gt; may be enough to move it away. If it is the size of a big boulder on the\n&gt; other hand, much more energy may be needed.\n&gt; &gt;\n&gt; &gt; All that is in your hands is to do sadhana with faith and persistence.\n&gt; And, remember, no effort is ever wasted. Every effort bears a fruit of\n&gt; comparable size eventually.\n&gt; &gt;\n&gt; &gt; Of course, you may be looking for a shortcut, but there is NONE. And\n&gt; sadhana is not so bad. Even before it solves your actual problem, the\n&gt; first thing sadhana does to you is: it gives you the courage to face the\n&gt; problem.\n&gt; &gt;\n&gt; &gt; * * *\n&gt; &gt;\n&gt; &gt; &gt; Doing sadhana and selfless surrender to the supreme being\n&gt; &gt; &gt; is of course ideal, but not tenable in the current times\n&gt; &gt; &gt; for the majority of the humans.\n&gt; &gt;\n&gt; &gt; Nothing is untenable. Though selfless surrender makes sadhana more\n&gt; efficient, sadhana without selfless surrender is also fine!\n&gt; &gt;\n&gt; &gt; Even if one&#39;s mind is filled with reasonable material desires\n&gt; (marriage, children, job, health etc), one can still do sadhana. Sadhana\n&gt; then takes care of one&#39;s material and spiritual needs and increases\n&gt; surrender and selflessness in one *over the time*.\n&gt; &gt;\n&gt; &gt; Bottomline: Good sadhana increases selfless surrender and selfless\n&gt; surrender promotes better sadhana. This is a positive feedback loop. One\n&gt; should somehow or the other break through. Break the impasse and just\n&gt; start some sadhana. Don&#39;t fear that something bad will happen or that\n&gt; you will not be able to do it. Just pick a sadhana and take the plunge!\n&gt; &gt;\n&gt; &gt; * * *\n&gt; &gt;\n&gt; &gt; &gt; And we need well-meaning people who are immersed in sadhana\n&gt; &gt; &gt; themselves to come forward and show us the way.\n&gt; &gt;\n&gt; &gt; That is what we are trying to do here..\n&gt; &gt;\n&gt; &gt; * * *\n&gt; &gt;\n&gt; &gt; Every mandala in RigVeda starts with hymns to Fire. Fire was\n&gt; worshipped by ancient people such as Zorostrains, Vedic rishis and\n&gt; ancient Greco-Romans. Even progressive modern paths such as Buddhism and\n&gt; Arya Samaj accept fire worship. Fire is a living representation of\n&gt; divinity on earth and spending time worshipping god in fire has a\n&gt; magical and purifying impact on one&#39;s consciousness.\n&gt; &gt;\n&gt; &gt; The proof of the pudding is in eating it. One can try homam every day\n&gt; or or every weekend for a few months and see for oneself what it does to\n&gt; one.\n&gt; &gt;\n